Implemented the fix in source only.

Changed:
- `gson/src/main/java/com/google/gson/internal/bind/TypeAdapterRuntimeTypeWrapper.java`
  - Adapter selection now treats delegating adapters as reflective when their serialization delegate is reflective.
- `gson/src/main/java/com/google/gson/Gson.java`
  - `FutureTypeAdapter` now exposes its serialization delegate.
- `gson/src/main/java/com/google/gson/internal/bind/TreeTypeAdapter.java`
  - Exposes serialization delegate for consistency with the same runtime-type selection logic.
- Added:
  - `gson/src/main/java/com/google/gson/internal/bind/SerializationDelegatingTypeAdapter.java`

Validation:
- Manually compiled Gson sources with `javac --release 8`.
- Verified the reported cyclic `Base` / `Sub` serialization case now outputs:
  - `{"f":{"i":2}}`

Note: `mvn -pl gson -DskipTests compile` is blocked in this environment by the configured Java release / warning-as-error setup, not by the source changes.
